<TITLE> HC clears way for mayor Mohiuddin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Thursday stayed for three months the government order barring Chittagong mayor ABM. Mohiuddin Chowdhury to resume office and allowing M Monjurul Alam to function as acting mayor. The bench of justices Nazmun Ara Sultana and Md Rezaul Haq passed the orders on a writ petition by Mohiuddin,. The court also ordered the government to explain why its order should not be declared illegal. Senior the assistant secretary at the ministry of local government on Oct. 13 issued an order barring Mohiuddin and allowing panel mayor Monjurul to function as mayor of Chittagong City Corporation. After the orders, Mohiuddin's counsel Harisadhan Dev Brahman told bdnews24.com that there was no more barrier to Mahiuddin resuming his functions as mayor. Barrister Amir Ul Islam and advocate Harisadhan Dev Brahman moved the writ petition, while deputy attorney general JBM Hasan opposed. bd
